distribution on <span class='cmr-12'>[0</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>1] </span>(K nearest-neighbor interactions), <span class='cmmi-12'>ḡ </span><span class='cmr-12'>= </span><span class='cmmi-12'>d</span><sup><span class='cmsy-8'>−</span><span class='cmr-8'>1</span></sup> <span class='cmex-10x-x-120'>∑</span><sub>
