</figure>
<h4 class='subsectionHead' id='the-punctuated-band-narrows-and-vanishes-with-increasing-d'><span class='titlemark'>4.2   </span> <a id='x1-140004.2'></a>The punctuated band narrows and vanishes with increasing <span class='cmmi-12'>d</span></h4>
<!-- l. 362 --><p class='noindent'>The central finding of this paper is that the punctuated regime occupies a <strong>narrow band in
β-space that shrinks and eventually vanishes</strong> as <span class='cmmi-12'>d </span>increases (Fig. <a href='#-punctuated-band-boundaries-and-deepbasin-condition-blue-circles-lower-phase-boundary-low-highest-with-nonfrozen-dynamics-rose-squares-upper-phase-boundary-high-lowest-with-zero-transitions-in-all-replicates-light-blue-bars-punctuated-band-width-range-of-between-the-two-boundaries-dashed-curves-fitted-scaling-laws-low-d-at-simulation-length-t-steps-the-intercept-shifts-with-tsee-sectionref-secdeepbasin-and-high-d-the-punctuated-band-light-blue-shading-is-visible-only-at-d-and-absent-at-d-the-theoretical-asymptotic-scaling-for-the-upper-boundary-is-d-corollarynashidab-the-fitted-exponent-reflects-finitesize-corrections-over-d-data-from-exp-replicates-steps-and-exp-replicates-steps-d-'>3<!-- tex4ht:ref: fig:band_boundaries  --></a>; Table <a href='#-regime-boundaries-and-punctuated-band-width-as-a-function-of-dimensiond-primary-experiment-exp-replicates-steps-for-d-exp-replicates-steps-for-d-punct-lowest-with-ratio-punctuatedband-lower-boundary-high-lowest-with-zero-transitions-in-allreplicates-frozen-boundary'>1<!-- tex4ht:ref: tab:regimes  --></a>). A precision
scan across <span class='cmmi-12'>d </span><span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>∈{</span><span class='cmr-12'>10</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>12</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>14</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>16</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>18</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>20</span><span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>} </span>(Exp. 2) reveals the vanishing in detail:
</p>   
<div class='table'>
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
