<a id='x1-380021'></a>
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
<!-- l. 1210 --><p class='noindent'><img alt='PIC' height='472' src='FigS1_extended_simulations.png' width='472' />
</p>
<figcaption class='caption'><span class='id'>Figure S1: </span><span class='content'><strong>Extended simulations at high dimensions</strong> (Exp. 3: 50 replicates <span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>× </span><span class='cmr-12'>2 </span><span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>× </span><span class='cmr-12'>10</span><sup><span class='cmr-8'>7</span></sup>
steps). Mean complete transitions per replicate at <span class='cmmi-12'>d </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 80</span>, <span class='cmr-12'>150</span>, and <span class='cmr-12'>300</span>. Error bars: bootstrap
95% CI. “F” marks frozen points (<span class='cmmi-12'>n</span><sub>tr</sub> <span class='cmr-12'>= 0 </span>across all replicates). No punctuated regime (ratio
<span class='cmmi-12'>&gt; </span><span class='cmr-12'>10</span>) is detected at any dimension. For all frozen points, the Poisson 95% upper bound on
the transition rate is <span class='cmmi-12'>&lt; </span><span class='cmr-12'>3 </span><span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>× </span><span class='cmr-12'>10</span><sup><span class='cmsy-8'>−</span><span class='cmr-8'>9</span></sup> per step.</span></figcaption><!-- tex4ht:label?: x1-380021  -->
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
   
</figure>
<figure class='figure' id='-selection-strength-scaling-exp-stasistransit-ratio-vs-under-three-s-coeff-rules-fixed-s-coeff-d-and-d-increasing-selection-strength-shifts-the-frozen-boundary-leftward-to-lower-without-restoring-a-punctuated-band-both-low-and-high-shift-together-preserving-or-reducing-band-width'> 

                                                                                          
                                                                                          
<a id='x1-380032'></a>
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
<!-- l. 1224 --><p class='noindent'><img alt='PIC' height='472' src='FigS2_selection_scaling.png' width='472' />
</p>
<figcaption class='caption'><span class='id'>Figure S2: </span><span class='content'><strong>Selection strength scaling (Exp. 5).</strong> Stasis/transit ratio vs. <span class='cmmi-12'>β </span>under three
<span class='cmmi-12'>s</span><sub>coeff</sub> rules: fixed (<span class='cmmi-12'>s</span><sub>coeff</sub> <span class='cmr-12'>= 5</span>), <span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>∝</span><img alt='√ --
  d' class='sqrt' src='paper_simulation_r199x.svg' />, and <span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>∝ </span><span class='cmmi-12'>d</span>. Increasing selection strength shifts the frozen
boundary leftward (to lower <span class='cmmi-12'>β</span>) without restoring a punctuated band. Both <span class='cmmi-12'>β</span><sub>low</sub><sup><span class='cmsy-8'>∗</span></sup> and <span class='cmmi-12'>β</span><sub>high</sub><sup><span class='cmsy-8'>∗</span></sup>
shift together, preserving or reducing band width.</span></figcaption><!-- tex4ht:label?: x1-380032  -->
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
   
</figure>
<figure class='figure' id='-threshold-sensitivity-exp-phase-diagrams-under-three-regime-classification-thresholds-ratio-and-background-shading-uses-the-same-color-scheme-as-fig-main-text-the-vanishing-punctuated-band-is-robust-across-all-thresholds-punctuated-dynamics-appear-only-at-d-in-all-cases'> 

                                                                                          
                                                                                          
<a id='x1-380043'></a>
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
<!-- l. 1237 --><p class='noindent'><img alt='PIC' height='472' src='FigS3_threshold_sensitivity.png' width='472' />
</p>
<figcaption class='caption'><span class='id'>Figure S3:  </span><span class='content'><strong>Threshold  sensitivity  (Exp. 6).</strong>  Phase  diagrams  under  three  regime
classification thresholds: ratio <span class='cmmi-12'>&gt; </span><span class='cmr-12'>5</span>, <span class='cmmi-12'>&gt; </span><span class='cmr-12'>10</span>, and <span class='cmmi-12'>&gt; </span><span class='cmr-12'>20</span>. Background shading uses the same color
scheme as Fig. 1 (main text). The vanishing punctuated band is robust across all thresholds;
punctuated dynamics appear only at <span class='cmmi-12'>d </span><span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>≤ </span><span class='cmr-12'>18 </span>in all cases.</span></figcaption><!-- tex4ht:label?: x1-380043  -->
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
   
</figure>
