</p>
<figcaption class='caption'><span class='id'>Figure S4:  </span><span class='content'><strong>Basin  boundary  (h<sup>∗</sup>)  sensitivity  (Exp. 7).</strong> Stasis/transit  ratio  vs. <span class='cmmi-12'>β </span>at
<span class='cmmi-12'>d </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 10</span>, <span class='cmr-12'>40</span>, and <span class='cmr-12'>150 </span>for <span class='cmmi-12'>h</span><sup><span class='cmsy-8'>∗</span></sup> <span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>∈{</span><span class='cmr-12'>0</span><span class='cmmi-12'>.</span><span class='cmr-12'>30</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>0</span><span class='cmmi-12'>.</span><span class='cmr-12'>35</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>0</span><span class='cmmi-12'>.</span><span class='cmr-12'>40</span><span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>}</span>. Regime structure is qualitatively unchanged
across all <span class='cmmi-12'>h</span><sup><span class='cmsy-8'>∗</span></sup> values. No punctuated regime emerges at <span class='cmmi-12'>d </span><span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>≥ </span><span class='cmr-12'>40 </span>for any <span class='cmmi-12'>h</span><sup><span class='cmsy-8'>∗</span></sup>.</span></figcaption><!-- tex4ht:label?: x1-380054  -->
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
   
</figure>
<figure class='figure' id='-alternative-basin-shapes-exp-stasistransit-ratio-vs-for-gaussian-and-polynomial-p-basin-forms-at-d-no-polynomial-shape-produces-a-punctuated-regime-at-any-dimension-even-at-d-where-gaussian-basins-yield-clear-punctuated-dynamics-ratio-all-polynomial-forms-remain-in-the-diffusive-regime-the-gaussian-shape-is-a-best-case-d-is-an-upper-bound-on-the-vanishing-threshold'> 

                                                                                          
                                                                                          
<a id='x1-380065'></a>
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
<!-- l. 1260 --><p class='noindent'><img alt='PIC' height='472' src='FigS5_alternative_shapes.png' width='472' />
</p>
<figcaption class='caption'><span class='id'>Figure S5: </span><span class='content'><strong>Alternative basin shapes (Exp. 8).</strong> Stasis/transit ratio vs. <span class='cmmi-12'>β </span>for Gaussian
and polynomial (<span class='cmmi-12'>p </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 1</span><span class='cmmi-12'>.</span><span class='cmr-12'>0</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>1</span><span class='cmmi-12'>.</span><span class='cmr-12'>5</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>2</span><span class='cmmi-12'>.</span><span class='cmr-12'>0</span>) basin forms at <span class='cmmi-12'>d </span><span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>∈{</span><span class='cmr-12'>10</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>14</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>18</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>20</span><span class='cmmi-12'>, </span><span class='cmr-12'>40</span><span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>}</span>. No polynomial shape
produces a punctuated regime at any dimension; even at <span class='cmmi-12'>d </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 10 </span>where Gaussian basins yield
clear punctuated dynamics (ratio <span class='cmr-12'>= 10</span><span class='cmmi-12'>.</span><span class='cmr-12'>6</span>–<span class='cmr-12'>1016</span>), all polynomial forms remain in the diffusive
regime. The Gaussian shape is a best case; <span class='cmmi-12'>d </span><span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>≈ </span><span class='cmr-12'>20 </span>is an upper bound on the vanishing
threshold.</span></figcaption><!-- tex4ht:label?: x1-380065  -->
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
   
</figure>
<figure class='figure' id='-preliminary-wrightfisher-population-dynamics-exp-regime-structure-at-three-n-settings-n-n-n-n-n-n-at-n-n-the-punctuated-regime-at-d-shifts-to-lower-and-is-absent-at-d-at-n-no-punctuated-regime-is-observed-at-any-dimension-population-effects-narrow-rather-than-rescue-the-punctuated-band-these-results-are-preliminary-largerscale-simulations-ne-are-needed-for-definitive-conclusions'> 

                                                                                          
                                                                                          
<a id='x1-380076'></a>
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
<!-- l. 1274 --><p class='noindent'><img alt='PIC' height='472' src='FigS6_wright_fisher.png' width='472' />
</p>
<figcaption class='caption'><span class='id'>Figure S6:  </span><span class='content'><strong>Preliminary  Wright–Fisher  population  dynamics  (Exp. 9).</strong>  Regime
structure at three <span class='cmmi-12'>Nμ </span>settings: <span class='cmmi-12'>Nμ </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 1 </span>(<span class='cmmi-12'>N </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 10</span>, <span class='cmmi-12'>μ </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 0</span><span class='cmmi-12'>.</span><span class='cmr-12'>1</span>); <span class='cmmi-12'>Nμ </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 1 </span>(<span class='cmmi-12'>N </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 100</span>, <span class='cmmi-12'>μ </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 0</span><span class='cmmi-12'>.</span><span class='cmr-12'>01</span>);
<span class='cmmi-12'>Nμ </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 10 </span>(<span class='cmmi-12'>N </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 100</span>, <span class='cmmi-12'>μ </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 0</span><span class='cmmi-12'>.</span><span class='cmr-12'>1</span>). At <span class='cmmi-12'>Nμ </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 1 </span>(<span class='cmmi-12'>N </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 10</span>), the punctuated regime at <span class='cmmi-12'>d </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 10 </span>shifts
to lower <span class='cmmi-12'>β </span>and is absent at <span class='cmmi-12'>d </span><span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>≥ </span><span class='cmr-12'>20</span>. At <span class='cmmi-12'>Nμ </span><span class='cmr-12'>= 10</span>, no punctuated regime is observed at any
dimension. Population effects narrow rather than rescue the punctuated band. These results
are preliminary; larger-scale simulations (<span class='cmmi-12'>N</span><sub><span class='cmmi-8'>e</span></sub> <span class='cmsy-10x-x-120'>∼ </span><span class='cmr-12'>10</span><sup><span class='cmr-8'>3</span></sup>–<span class='cmr-12'>10</span><sup><span class='cmr-8'>6</span></sup>) are needed for definitive conclusions.</span></figcaption><!-- tex4ht:label?: x1-380076  -->
                                                                                          
                                                                                          
   
</figure>
 
